de.bioforscher.singa.mathematics.concepts

Interface Multipliable<NumberConcept extends Multipliable<NumberConcept>>

  • Type Parameters:
    NumberConcept - A reference to the class or interface which the multiplication will result in.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LabeledMatrix<LabelType>, Matrix, Ring<RingType>, Vector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Interval, LabeledRegularMatrix, LabeledSymmetricMatrix, RegularMatrix, RegularVector, Scalar, SquareMatrix, SymmetricMatrix, Vector2D, Vector3D

    public interface Multipliable<NumberConcept extends Multipliable<NumberConcept>>
    The "multiplication" operation can be any commutative and associative binary operation on a number concept. Generally it is equivalent to adding as many copies of one of them (multiplicand) as the value of the other one (multiplier).

    Multiplication is commutative, meaning that order does not matter, and it is associative, meaning that when one multiplies more than two numbers, the order in which multiplication is performed does not matter. The multiplication of the "Multiplicative One Element" does not change the value of the result. Any number multiplied by the "Multiplicative Zero Element" will return the Zero element.

    See Also:
    Wikipedia: Multiplication
